## System-Level Reasoning & Incentive Awareness

I don’t assume I know a system’s real problems upfront. My value lies in identifying where issues *might* emerge when incentives, verification mechanisms, and real-world behavior interact.  
(“Which drivers are critical, and what happens when they approach their extreme edges?”)

Claiming certainty ahead of time is hubris. What works is building clarity around possible future scenarios and preparing for the moment they materialize. Surfacing risks early, even if they later turn out to be benign, is part of responsible product leadership.

As a PM, my role is not to dictate solutions, but to structure team communication, keep teams aligned across engineering, operations, and support (full DevOps chain), and ensure decisions and assumptions can be audited, revised, and reversed.

